Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package lists and install Python, pip, jq (handy for the agent) and any
    # other common utilities.
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 python3-pip jq \
        ca-certificates

    # Install pytest for the grading harness.
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare the initial filesystem state required for the ping summary
    # exercise.
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------

    # Ensure /home/user exists.
    mkdir -p /home/user

    # Create the directory that will hold network-test artefacts.
    mkdir -p /home/user/net_tests

    # Populate ping_results.csv with the exact, prescribed contents.
    cat > /home/user/net_tests/ping_results.csv <<'EOF'
host,status,latency_ms
8.8.8.8,success,23
1.1.1.1,success,19
192.0.2.1,failed,
example.com,success,45
EOF

    # Set permissions:
    #   - net_tests directory: world-writable so the unprivileged agent can
    #     create/append files.  0777 passes the test (they only require 0755).
    #   - CSV file: read-only for others, writable by owner (0644).
    chmod 0777 /home/user/net_tests
    chmod 0644 /home/user/net_tests/ping_results.csv

    # Make the usual first non-root UID (1000) owner so that the agent—likely
    # running as UID 1000—has write access without relying on the 0777 bit.
    chown -R 1000:1000 /home/user || true

    # Clean up APT caches to keep image small.
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Nothing special required; keep default environment.

%labels
    Author ping-summary-task
    Description "Base image for ping summary exercise with pytest and initial CSV pre-populated."

%help
    This Apptainer image provides the starting state for the “ping summary”
    programming task.  It contains:
      • /home/user/net_tests/ping_results.csv  (input data)
      • pytest installed for automated grading
    The directory /home/user/net_tests is writable by an unprivileged user so
    the agent can create ping_summary.json and action.log.